rs and four contributors that have spent only a \"minor portion\" of their careers with the Dolphins, and have been enshrined primarily with other teams, have also been enshrined in the Pro Football Hall of Fame.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\" style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Miami Dolphins}};\"|'''Miami Dolphins Hall of Famers'''\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\" style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Miami Dolphins}};\"|Players\n|-\n! style=\"width:30px;\"|No.\n! style=\"width:130px;\"|Name\n! style=\"width:130px;\"|College\n! style=\"width:130px;\"|Position\n! style=\"width:50px;\"|Season(s)\n! style=\"width:50px;\"|Inducted\n|-\n| 42 || '''[[Paul Warfield]]''' || [[Ohio State]] || [[Wide Receiver|WR]] || 1970\u20131974 || 1983\n|-\n| 39 || '''[[Larry Csonka]]''' || [[Syracuse University|Syracuse]] || [[Fullback (gridiron football)|FB]] || 1968\u20131974, 1979 || 1987\n|-\n| 62 || '''[[Jim Langer]]''' || [[South Dakota State University|South Dakota State]] || [[Center (American football)|C]] || 1970\u20131979 || 1987\n|-\n| 12 || '''[[Bob Griese]]''' || [[Purdue Boilermakers|Purdue]] || [[Quarterback|QB]] || 1967\u20131980 || 1990\n|-\n| 66 || '''[[Larry Little]]''' || [[Bethune\u2013Cookman Wildcats football|Bethune-Cookman]] || [[Guard (American football)|G]] || 1969\u20131980 || 1993\n|-\n| 57 || '''[[Dwight Stephenson]]''' || [[Alabama Crimson Tide football|Alabama]] || [[Center (American football)|C]] || 1980\u20131987 || 1998\n|-\n| 85 || '''[[Nick Buoniconti]]''' || [[University of Notre Dame|Notre Dame]] || [[Linebacker|LB]] || 1969\u20131974, 1976 || 2001\n|-\n| 13 || '''[[Dan Marino]]''' || [[Pittsburgh Panthers football|Pittsburgh]] || [[Quarterback|QB]] || 1983\u20131999 || 2005\n|-\n| 99 || '''[[Jason Taylor (American football)|Jason Taylor]]''' || [[Akron Zips football|Akron]] || [[Defensive End|DE]] || 1997\u20132007, 2009, 2011 || 2017\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\" style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Miami Dolphins}};\"|Coaches and Executives\n|-\n!