e\" style=\"font-size: 80%\" width=align=\n|+ Busiest domestic routes to and from Nur-Sultan by weekly flights (2020)\n|-\n| Rank\n! Region\n! City\n! Airport(s)\n![[IATA airport code|IATA]]\n! Weekly Departures\n! Airlines\n|-\n| 1.\n| {{flagicon|Almaty}} [[Almaty]]\n| [[Almaty]]\n| [[Almaty International Airport]]\n| ALA\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 144\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |{{nowrap|Air Astana, Bek Air, FlyArystan, Qazaq Air, SCAT Airlines}}\n|-\n| 2.\n| {{flagicon|Kazakhstan}} [[Shymkent]]\n| [[Shymkent]]\n| {{nowrap|[[Shymkent International Airport]]}}\n| CIT\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 41\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | Air Astana, Bek Air, FlyArystan, Qazaq Air, SCAT Airlines\n|-\n| 3.\n| {{flagicon|Kazakhstan}} [[Atyrau Region]]\n| [[Atyrau]]\n| [[Atyrau Airport|Atyrau International Airport]]\n| GUW\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" | 33\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" | Air Astana, Bek Air, Qazaq Air, SCAT Airlines\n|-\n| 4.\n| {{flagicon|Kazakhstan}} [[East Kazakhstan Region]]\n| {{nowrap|[[Oskemen]]}}\n| [[Oskemen Airport]]\n| UKK\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 30\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | Air Astana, Bek Air, Qazaq Air, SCAT Airlines\n|-\n| 5.\n| {{flagicon|Kazakhstan}} [[Aktobe Region]]\n| [[Aktobe]]\n| [[Aktobe International Airport]]\n| AKX\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" | 29\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" |  Air Astana, Bek Air, Qazaq Air, SCAT Airlines\n|-\n| 6.\n| {{flagicon|Kazakhstan}} [[Mangystau Region]]\n| [[Aktau]]\n| [[Aktau Airport|Aktau International Airport]]\n| SCO\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 19\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |   Air Astana, Bek Air, SCAT Airlines\n|-\n| 7.\n| {{flagicon|Kazakhstan}} [[Jambyl Region]]\n| [[Taraz]]\n| [[Taraz Airport|Aulie-Ata International Airport]]\n| DMB\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 19\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | FlyArystan, SCAT Airlines\n|-\n| 8.\n| {{flagicon|Kazakhstan}} [[Kostanay Region]]\n| [[Kostanay]]\n| [[Kostanay Airport]]\n| KSN\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 17\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | FlyArystan, Qazaq Air, SCAT Airlines\n|-\n| 9.\n| {{flagicon|Kazakhstan}} [[Kyzylorda Region]]\n| [[Kyzylorda]]\n| [[Kyzylorda Airport]]\n| KZO\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 13\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | Air Astana, Bek Air\n|-\n| 10.\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|Kazakhstan}} [[West Kazakhstan Region]]}}\n| [[Oral, Kazakhstan|Oral]]\n| [[Oral Ak Zhol Airport]]\n| URA\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 10\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | Air Astana, Bek Air\n|-\n| colspan=7 align=\"right\"| ''Sources: Statistics<ref name=\"Flightradar24\">{{cite web|url=https://www.flightradar24.com/data/airports/tse |title=Nursultan Nazarbayev International Airport|publisher=Flightradar24|accessdate=2019-10-14}}</ref>''\n|}\n</center>\n\n<center>\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size: 80%\" width=align=\n|+ Busiest [[Commonwealth of Independent States|CIS]] routes to and from Nur-Sultan by weekly flights (2020)\n|-\n| Rank\n! Country\n! City\n! Airport(s)\n![[IATA airport code|IATA]]\n! Weekly Departures\n! Airlines\n|-\n| 1.\n| {{flagicon|Moscow}} [[Moscow]]<br />{{nowrap|{{flagicon|Moscow Oblast}} [[Moscow Oblast]]}}<br />{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Russia]]\n| [[Moscow]]\n| {{nowrap|[[Sheremetyevo International Airport]]}},<br>[[Domodedovo International Airport]],<br>[[Vnukovo International Airport]],<br>[[Zhukovsky International Airport]]\n| SVO<br>DME<br>VKO<br>ZIA\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 31\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | Aeroflot,<br> Air Astana, S7 Airlines (begins {{date|2020-5-26}}),<ref>{{cite web |title= CAPA - Centre for Aviation - S7 Airlines to launch Moscow-Nur Sultan service from May-2020\n|url= https://centreforaviation.com/news/s7-airlines-to-launch-moscow-nur-sultan-service-from-may-2020-957171|accessdate=23 November 2019}}</ref><br>SCAT Airlines,<br> FlyArystan \n|-\n| 2.\n| {{flagicon|Uzbekistan}} [[Uzbekistan]]\n| [[Tashkent]]\n| [[Islam Karimov Tashkent International Airport]]\n|